"Harold Charles Schonberg (November 29, 1915 \u2013 July 26, 2003) was an American music critic and journalist, best known for his contributions to The New York Times. In 1971, he became the first music critic to win the Pulitzer Prize for Criticism. In addition, Schonberg reviewed mysteries and thrillers for The New York Times under the name Newgate Callender for nearly a quarter of a century. He also wrote a number of books on music, and one on chess.\n\n"